{
  "stem": "21550.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they waited there for the big train, the freight trains to come.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And unfortunately for my mother, as soon as she was brought to this siding, they put her in the train, into the train, and picked her up right away so she wouldn't be rescued.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[DRINKS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was the only-- the only way.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everybody went the same way to this-- to this particular siding, which was almost in the middle of the city, which-- it was-- you know, it was guarded by the German SS.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and there was Jewish police also, which helped the Germans.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in the-- the first thing was we had to leave the apartment we lived in.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was this section of the town-- this section of Warsaw was not included in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So at the beginning, we exchanged apartments.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were Gentiles living in parts of the city which was incorporated into the ghetto and some Jews were living in parts which were out-- excluded from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they had to swap the apartments somehow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a-- quite a big exchange going on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we had to move from there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I remember it was-- winter was coming, and we had some coal prepared for the winter.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So every time we moved, we had to drag the coal along, which was quite an ordeal, but we had to have it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we moved about four times, because every time they changed the ghetto, they excluded a street or they incorporated a street, there was big changes.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the general feeling was that they-- Warsaw is a big city, wouldn't suffer as much as the little towns and the villages, because there was a-- just-- just by the power of the-- of the masses, amount-- number of people living there.",
      "word_count": 43
    }
  ],
